success.question_text: At the same rate, how long will it take two men to dig four holes?
success.question_category_path: General Ability / Non-Verbal Reasoning / Problem Solving

stimulus_2.text: It takes 4 hours for four men to dig eight holes.

review_1.column_1_text: Solution

review_3.column_1_text:
In 4 hours, four men dig eight holes. By division, in 1 hour, four men dig two holes.

By division, in 1 hour, two men dig one hole.

By multiplication, in 4 hours, two men dig four holes.

By halving the number of men and halving the number of holes the time taken will not change.

Tip

Show your working so that you can check the steps you have used to arrive at your answer.

II. Sharon and Brett are neighbours.

III. Sharon and Sam are twins.
